description:
Com uma vasta experiência no mercado eletroeletrônico, a Prosperity esta sempre inovando. Temos o prazer de apresentar o conceito de vendas de soluções para o mercado de montagens de placas SMD e PTH.

Contamos com uma matriz em Indaiatuba - SP e filiais em Orlando - USA e Shenzhen - China, a fim de dar suporte aos negócios nacionais e internacionais da empresa, visando desenvolver parcerias confiáveis e duradouras.

Nosso principal objetivo é oferecer aos nossos clientes e fornecedores, serviços, produtos e soluções de alta qualidade, relacionados à automação em linha de montagem de componentes eletrônicos, SMD e PTH, em placas de circuito impresso, para empresas de pequeno, médio e grande porte. Contamos com uma equipe de vendedores técnicos e engenheiros extremamente capacitados, para dar todo o suporte necessário aos nossos clientes, garantindo a melhor relação custo x beneficio, bem como suporte técnico para instalação e treinamento em todos os equipamentos que comercializamos.

description:
Hello, I'm Andy. My goal is to create entertaining videos mostly, but not only, for people who love cars & crashes. 

All the videos you'll find in this channel are recorded & edited by me and my sidekick, George, who helps with parts of the editing.
This channel is our full-time job. We're devoting a minimum of 100 hours per week to bring you the best BeamNG drive videos.

How we work:

Creating these videos is a lot harder & time consuming than you might think but it is what makes us and, hopefully, you happy!
We are playing BeamNG.drive, a PC Game featuring the ultimate soft-body physics and realism. 

The process, step by step:

- Recording the clips with Action! (10-15 hours, sometimes 15+)
- Editing & synchronizing the clips with music & addition of captions / sound effects - Premiere Pro (5-10 hours)  
- Descriptions, Thumbnails etc.  (2 hours)

We’re uploading 4 Videos per week on Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday & Sunday. Stay up to date by Subscribing!
Thank you :)

Spending my life track-side, breathing gasoline and recording the greatest sounding machines since 2009. So if you're a petrolhead and you love motorsport, this may be the right Youtube channel for you!

🎧For an even greater sense of immersion, you can also find videos recorded using binaural microphones, labelled as ''[3D Binaural Audio]'' in the title

📸 I couldn't help but fall in love with photography too, sooner or later. You can find my works on Flickr and on my Instagram account @ste19bozzy92

To our amazing viewers and the RC community: thank you. Your encouragement, feedback, and enthusiasm over the years have turned this small hobby channel into a worldwide community. We’re humbled and grateful for every comment, every share, and every fellow hobbyist who’s joined us on this journey. You are the reason RCSparks Studio has become one of the most vibrant RC communities on YouTube, and we never forget that. 

If you’re new here, welcome to the family! We hope our story inspires you to chase your own creative passions – whether it’s building your first RC kit or starting a channel of your own. We’re always evolving and dreaming up the next big adventure, but we’ll never lose sight of why we started: to have fun, be creative, and share it with all of you. The road ahead is full of new RC adventures, and we couldn’t be more excited to have you along for the ride. Thank you for being part of our journey and for keeping the RC spark alive!

description:
AddMe.Lab is the Additive Manufacturing laboratory established in 2014 at the Department of Mechanical Engineering of the Politecnico di Milano. 
AddMe.Lab was born with the idea of stimulating the collaboration and the generation of ideas among the different research groups active in the Department specialized in product design, materials, process technologies, as well as with students and professionals. The result is a unique center for experimentation, the creation of new process concepts, and the implementation of metal additive manufacturing techniques for different sectors such as mechanics, biomedicine, aerospace, oil & gas, and industrial design. 
AddMe.Lab processes include selective laser melting (SLM), laser metal deposition (LMD), laser mertal wire deposition (LMWD), electron beam melting (EBM), binder jetting, and metal fused deposition modeling.

description:
What is PNR Status?
PNR (Passenger Name Record) is a 10 digit code written on top-left corner of a ticket. It is a travel record of an individual or a group of individuals, maintained in CRS (Central Reservation System) database. This code is generated only when the CRS gets full data of journey like passenger's name, gender, age, train number, journey class, berth preference, contact link, etc. It is a "follow-up" process by which passengers are able to get updates about the status of their journey. This code is of great use to passengers, whose tickets are not confirmed. It helps them to check whether their tickets got confirmed or not.

You can check your ticket' reservation status from our site: https://www.pnrstatusbuzz.in/

We license out our stock music for use in media such as: Films, Video games, Stage productions, Toys and Items, Commercials, Podcasts and much more; Licensing is done via our own in-house stock music licensing website, www.Shockwave-Sound.com.

We source and record our own classical music, pop music, rock, disco, funk, hip-hop, folk, country, and just about every music style you'll have heard of.

description:
Hi all!!!

My name is Jim and I'm the creator of this channel. This is my full time job and my mission is to bring you the highest quality and of high standard editing BeamNG drive videos with unique, meaningful and fun content.

BeamNG drive is the most realistic driving game that mimics every component of a vehicle in real time resulting in lifelike behavior.

All my videos are created by myself using the following programs : GeForce Experience for recording, Adobe Premiere Pro for editing and synchronizing the initially raw footage and Photoshop for thumbnails.

My weekly process consists of:
- Recording my clips ( 30 - 40 hours )
- Editing my clips ( 18 - 24 hours ) That includes editing in image, music, captions and sound effects.
-Thumbnails, description etc. roughly 10 hours.

I upload 3 times a week every Tuesday, Friday and Sunday, at 5pm GMT

Join me and be part of this adventure. 

Subscribe and stay tuned!

description: The California High-Speed Rail Authority is responsible for planning, designing, building and operation of the first high-speed rail system in the nation. California high-speed rail will connect the mega-regions of the state, contribute to economic development and a cleaner environment, create jobs and preserve agricultural and protected lands. The system will run from San Francisco to the Los Angeles basin in under three hours at speeds capable of over 200 miles per hour. The system will eventually extend to Sacramento and San Diego, totaling 800 miles with up to 24 stations. In addition, the Authority is working with regional partners to implement a state-wide rail modernization plan that will invest billions of dollars in local and regional rail lines to meet the state's 21st century transportation needs.

My Videos are idea based and are NOT used to teach or instruct. Sometimes I get the science wrong and don't mind being corrected.

My videos are solely what I am doing with my model the Syma X8 Venture that I have added the Altitude Hold receiver board and will continue to modify with different receiver boards and Flight Controllers. 

I use this chassis to install different receiver boards from different Manufactures and Models thus getting the flight modes and characteristics from that model. By getting the corresponding transmitters I can use my Syma X8 Venture as that model would. 

Eventually I will put an APM flight controller in this chassis and use my Turnigy 9xr Pro ....... but for now Im learning and having fun.

description:
Passionately documenting the Indian Railways for the present and future Generations.This is my hobby Channel showcasing mainly videos of the Indian Railways- 
The total track length of network is 119,640 km (74,340 mi) while the total route length of the network is 66,687 km (41,437 mi). Track sections are rated for speeds ranging from 80 to 200 km/h (50 to 124 mph), though trains don't really clock speeds of 200 km/h. Maximum speed attained by passenger trains is 177 km/h-180 km/h (110 mph).


A perfect place for all the Train lovers of all age groups who love enjoy watching High Quality Train Videos.

Enjoy the Content , Like, Comment , Subscribe and Share it with your Circles who have the same passion for Trains.

Suggestions are always Welcome. 
INDIAN TRAINS

description:
The official BUGATTI YouTube Channel

Since its foundation in 1909 by Ettore Bugatti, the brand has been at the pinnacle of the automotive industry, creating the world’s most powerful and luxurious automobiles from its home in Molsheim, France. In the 1920s, BUGATTI became known for its racing successes as well as in the 1930s for Jean Bugatti’s elegant touring cars. In 1991, the EB110 premiered and set new benchmarks for sports car performance. 

With the introduction of the VEYRON 16.4 in 2005, BUGATTI created an entirely new segment: the hyper sports car, becoming the first production model to break through 1,000 PS and 400 km/h. In 2016, the CHIRON once again redefined speed and usability, culminating in a 1,600 PS version breaking the 300mph barrier. 

Today, BUGATTI is part of the BUGATTI Rimac Group and well underway with the development of the next-generation of BUGATTI hyper sports cars, true to Ettore’s motto "If comparable, it is no longer BUGATTI."

description:
Hello and welcome to the BeamNG-FUN YouTube channel! As you'll see, I have a passion for storytelling and experimenting using the BeamNG.drive physics simulation sandbox. This channel exists as a platform for me to share my stories, experiments and other mayhem created in BeamNG.drive.

I create my videos by first recording many hours of my own unique and custom scenarios within BeamNG.drive using OBS Studio. I then spend a significant amount of time editing these clips in Davinci Resolve to create a story before finally uploading the completed video to YouTube. This is a long process and while I strive to upload videos on a consistent basis, I typically average a few uploads per week.

Please note that the creators of BeamNG.drive allows for game owners to create, upload, and monetize gameplay videos on YouTube. More info on this can be found here: https://wiki.beamng.com/BeamNG_FAQ#Can_I_upload_and_monetize_my_BeamNG.drive_videos_on_Youtube.3F

description: America is big with a wide variety of places ranging from beautiful to historical to whimsical. During my travels across America, I am going to take you to lots of these places. All of this was channeled into his critically acclaimed double album, Survivor’s Remorse in 2022 which Rolling Stone called, “another potent look into his rattled, conflicted psyche that also doubles as a celebration of his 10-year run as one of the most enduring young rappers to come out of Chicago’s drill scene.” Following up from his 2023 mixtape, Strictly For My Fans 2, and earning  Platinum and Gold plaques for Nardo Wick’s “Who Want Smoke” and his late friend Young Dolph’s “One Scale” that same year, Herbo aims to reach his full potential as an artist with his celebratory offering for the summertime, Big Swerv. The album is executive produced by longtime collaborators Southside and Big Oz.
G Herbo's four albums,”PTSD,” “25,” “Swervo,” and his debut, “Humble Beast” all reached the Billboard Top 200 chart.

description:
Managing director and founder of Racelogic, designer of the VBOX, electronics engineer, programmer, physicist and amateur racing driver with 7 Championship wins. Racelogic are experts in position, speed and orientation measurement, both outdoors with GPS and indoors with centimetre accuracy or even a combination of both.

At the weekends, I Race Andy Rouse's 1989 BTCC RS500, a Cobra Daytona, Chevron B8, Jaguar E-Type, Ford Falcon and a VW FunCup. 

Our new VIPS indoor positioning system is ideal for tracking moving robots and now being used in virtual production for camera tracking. Racelogic supply almost all of the vehicle companies in the world with speed and position test equipment, many of the major technology companies with our LabSat GPS simulator, and a growing number of film companies for virtual production camera tracking. Customers include Google, Apple, SpaceX, Tesla, Ferrari, BMW, Garmin, Trimble, NASA, Amazon, Samsung, VW, Porsche and many more.

description:
Sandia National Laboratories safeguards the nation's nuclear stockpile and helps the country solve some of its most pressing engineering problems in homeland security, energy, and basic research. 

Its roots lie in World War II's Manhattan Project. Its history reflects the changing national security needs of postwar America. 

Sandia's original emphasis on ordnance engineering — turning the nuclear physics packages created by Los Alamos and Lawrence Livermore National Laboratories into deployable weapons — expanded into new areas as national security requirements changed. 

In addition to ensuring the safety and reliability of the stockpile, Sandia applied the expertise it acquired in weapons work to a variety of related areas such as energy research, supercomputing, treaty verification, nanotechnology, and nonproliferation.

description: I live in China for half the year and in Canada the other half. This channel features my impressions of living in Nanning, China. Nanning is a city of 6.6 million people located in the province of Guangxi in southwest China. It is sub-tropical and close to Vietnam, Thailand, Cambodia, Mynnamar. The many ethnic groups in Guangxi are related to ethnic groups in southwest Asia, e.g., the Dai people in Guangxi are the ancestral people of the Thais. My videos show the daily life of Nanning  as well experiences from my travels to neighboring cities and provinces, most notably Yunnan. I am a photographer, teacher and actor (a partial film resumé is under listed under Wally Houn on IMDb.)

description:
Dedicamos este canal al idioma inglés. Nos orientamos a los padres, maestros y niños de todo el mundo que quieren aprender una lengua extranjera compleja y diferente. 

 Para construir este camino hay múltiples formas de hacerlo, pero estamos comprometidos a dar un enfoque lúdico, comunicativo y muy educativo, basado en la canción como el núcleo de nuestra metodología. Creemos que la música es la herramienta perfecta que combina la clave de la emoción, la intuición y el movimiento para la creación de un aprendizaje significativo del inglés. 

 Nuestros hijos y nuestros alumnos aprenden a través del movimiento, la reiteración de oraciones y sentimientos que estas les evocan. Conque estamos trabajando sin descanso para estar refiriéndose recursos didácticos innovadores y originales.

description:
World Marine Offshore is a Danish offshore shipping company established in 2012 in the port of Esbjerg to meet the increasing demand for cost effective, safe and efficient crew and cargo transfer vessels.

We specialize in offshore crew transfer, cargo transfer, guard operation, rescue support and chase operation.

World Marine Offshore is operated from Denmark but have focus on the entire world. We currently operate in Denmark, Germany, Great Britain, Netherlands, Belgium and France.

The Company’s goal is to be the preferred provider of quality-assured supply services to offshore companies, both national and international. The Company aims to safeguard its long-term perspective through a balanced chartering strategy that ensures a basic cash flow combined with an assessed exposure to the spot market.

description:
Welcome to JimLiElevators: My name is Jim and I am an elevator photographer based in central Texas. I have always loved elevators when I was a kid. Been filming since 2005. I present to you videos of elevators that are both vintage and modern. Not only that I film elevators, but I've also been interested into trains as well. I'll occasionally upload animated elevators because I've had a lot of fun making them. So with that said, I hope you enjoy your visit to my channel.

Thanks so much for your loyal viewership. I take pride in keeping this channel clean for all ages. I am also a born Christian, so I want to keep it pleasing to Jesus as well! “For God so loved the world that he gave his only son that believes in him shall not perish but have eternal life. John 3:16."

I'm also thankful to Andrew Reams (DieselDucy) who's the deepest inspiration towards me to start this channel. That said, make sure you subscribe. Thanks and have a great day! :D
